Problem Statement¶

A hedge fund uses 6 financial factors to predict the alpha signal in a stock. This alpha signal is used to make purchase decisions about the stock. The hedge fund now collected and tagged microblogging data for sentiment from the Social Media platform called StockTwits. The hedge fund has anonymyzed the data, which contains 7 stock factors and an alpha signal. This alpha signal is generated using a near perfect algorithmic trading strategy. Unfortunately, the number of stock factors, collected to run that strategy, are extremely high and have to be collected from a large number of data vendors at a high price.

Business understanding¶

A hedge fund's purpose is to maximize investor returns and eliminate risk. When deciding the value of a company, it's important to follow the news. For example, a product recall or natural disaster in a company's product chain. You want to be able to turn this information into a signal. Currently, the number of stock factors, collected to run that strategy, are extremely high and have to be collected from a large number of data vendors at a high price. If we use social networking plateform to understand the more about hedge funds and apply strategy to predict the alpha value along with stock factors , can reduce the expanse ratio of the company.

Proposed solution¶

  • Perform EDA on JSON data to get more insight about the stock twots
  • Perform text sentiments Analysis on stock twits
  • Apply Deep neural network and ML learaning both to get best sentiment score of tweets and choose best one
  • Merge Json data with hedge fund csv
  • Apply ML Algorithm to predict the alpha value

Comparison Matrix¶

  • Highest Accuracy in Text sentiment Analysis, we have got in logistic regession 81, also get more accurate result in Deep neural network(RNN) is 80.2

Pre Process the Tweets¶

Convert all message to lower case¶

Replace URLs with a space in the message¶

Replace ticker symbols with a space. The ticker symbols are any stock symbol that starts with $.¶

Replace StockTwits usernames with a space. The usernames are any word that starts with @.¶

Replace alphanumeric charcter with space¶

Replace all special char with sapce¶

In [39]:
def Tokenize_and_lemmetize(t):
    """
    This function tokenize the tweets and then use WordNetLemmatizer for grouping together
    the different inflected forms of a word so they can be analysed as a single item
    """                      
    words = word_tokenize(t)
    words = [word for word in words if word not in stopwords_english]
    #lemmatize each word to its lemma
    lemmatizer = WordNetLemmatizer()
    lemma_words = [lemmatizer.lemmatize(i) for i in words]
    filtered = ' '.join(lemma_words)  
    return filtered

# Calculating positive score 
def positive_score(text):
    numPosWords = 0
    #ss = token_lemt(text)
    rawToken = tokenizer(text)
    
    for word in rawToken:
        if word in positiveWordList:
            numPosWords  += 1
    
    sumPos = numPosWords
    return sumPos
In [57]:
# Calculating Negative score
def negative_word(text):
    numNegWords=0
    #ss = token_lemt(text)
    rawToken = tokenizer(text)
    
    for word in rawToken:
        if word in negativeWordList:
            numNegWords -=1
    sumNeg = numNegWords 
    sumNeg = sumNeg * -1
    return sumNeg
In [58]:
def tokenizer(text):
    #text = text.lower()
    tokenizer = RegexpTokenizer(r'\w+')
    tokens = tokenizer.tokenize(text)
    filtered_words = list(filter(lambda token: token not in stopwords_english, tokens))
    return filtered_words
In [59]:
# Calculating polarity score
def polarity_score(positiveScore, negativeScore):
    pol_score = (positiveScore - negativeScore) / ((positiveScore + negativeScore) + 0.000001)
    return pol_score

from wordcloud import WordCloud

def word_cloud_form(list):
  #convert list to string and generate
  vocabulary = [each_word for sub_list in vocabulary_lists for each_word in sub_list]
  unique_string=(" ").join(vocabulary)
  wordcloud = WordCloud(width = 1000, 
                      height = 500,
                      collocations = False
                     ).generate(unique_string)
  plt.figure(figsize=(15,8))
  plt.imshow(wordcloud)
  plt.axis("off")
  plt.show()
  plt.close()

def token_lemt_token_only(var):
    #v = clean_data(var)
    words = word_tokenize(var)
    #words = [word for word in words if word not in stopwords_english]
    #lemma_words = [lemmatizer.lemmatize(i, get_wordnet_pos(i)) for i in words]
    lemmatizer = WordNetLemmatizer()
    lemma_words = [lemmatizer.lemmatize(i) for i in words]
    #filtered = ' '.join(lemma_words)
    return lemma_words
